# /diagram — Diagramas Mermaid

## Uso
```
/diagram [tipo] [contexto]
```

**Tipos**: `components` | `flow` | `sequence` | `er` | `state`

## Fases

### Fase 0 — Reconhecimento
1. Entender o contexto solicitado (modulo, feature, fluxo)
2. Ler codigo relevante para extrair componentes e relacoes reais

### Fase 1 — Gerar Diagrama

Salvar em: `{{paths.docsRoot}}/diagrams/{contexto}-{tipo}.md`

#### Componentes (C4 simplificado)
```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Modulo X"
        A[Componente A] --> B[Componente B]
        B --> C[Componente C]
    end
```

#### Fluxo de Dados
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Input --> Process --> Output
    Process --> |erro| ErrorHandler
```

#### Sequencia
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Usuario
    participant F as Frontend
    participant B as Backend
    U->>F: Acao
    F->>B: Request
    B-->>F: Response
    F-->>U: Feedback
```

#### Entidade-Relacionamento
```mermaid
erDiagram
    ENTITY_A ||--o{ ENTITY_B : "relacao"
    ENTITY_B {
        string id PK
        string name
    }
```

#### Maquina de Estados
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Inicial
    Inicial --> Processando : evento
    Processando --> Concluido : sucesso
    Processando --> Erro : falha
```

## Checklist
- [ ] Diagrama reflete a realidade do codigo
- [ ] Labels claros e descritivos
- [ ] Direcao de fluxo logica
- [ ] Sintaxe Mermaid valida
{{else}}
# /diagram — Mermaid Diagrams

## Usage
```
/diagram [type] [context]
```

**Types**: `components` | `flow` | `sequence` | `er` | `state`

## Phases

### Phase 0 — Reconnaissance
1. Understand the requested context (module, feature, flow)
2. Read relevant code to extract real components and relationships

### Phase 1 — Generate Diagram

Save to: `{{paths.docsRoot}}/diagrams/{context}-{type}.md`

#### Components (simplified C4)
```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Module X"
        A[Component A] --> B[Component B]
        B --> C[Component C]
    end
```

#### Data Flow
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Input --> Process --> Output
    Process --> |error| ErrorHandler
```

#### Sequence
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant B as Backend
    U->>F: Action
    F->>B: Request
    B-->>F: Response
    F-->>U: Feedback
```

#### Entity-Relationship
```mermaid
erDiagram
    ENTITY_A ||--o{ ENTITY_B : "relationship"
    ENTITY_B {
        string id PK
        string name
    }
```

#### State Machine
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Initial
    Initial --> Processing : event
    Processing --> Completed : success
    Processing --> Error : failure
```

## Checklist
- [ ] Diagram reflects code reality
- [ ] Clear and descriptive labels
- [ ] Logical flow direction
- [ ] Valid Mermaid syntax
{{/if}}
